quizzes.question:
Type in the default values for the parameters of the function volume, suppose the parameter a has default value 2; the parameter b has default value 3; and the parameter c has default value 5.
[!raw!]
int volume(int a = {0}, int b {1} 3, int c = 5)
{
  return a * b * c;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Default Values for Parameters[/h1]

When defining a function, you can specify a [b]default [/b]value for each of the last parameters. If the corresponding argument is missing when you call a function, it uses the [b]default [/b]value.

To do this, use the assignment operator to assign values to the arguments in the function definition, as shown in this example.[code format="cpp" ]int sum(int a, int [b]b=42[/b]) {
  int result = a + b;
  return (result);
}[/code]
This assigns a default value of 42 to the [b]b[/b] parameter. If we call the function without passing the value for the b parameter, the default value will be used.[code format="cpp" codeId="244"]int main() {
  int x = 24;
  int y = 36;

  //calling the function with both parameters
  int result = sum(x, y);
  cout << result << endl;
  //Outputs 60

  //calling the function without b
  result = sum(x);
  cout <<  result << endl;
   //Outputs 66

  return 0;
}[/code]
[note]The second call to the function does not pass a value for the second parameter, and the default value of 42 is used, instead.[/note]

quizzes.question:
What is the output of the following code?
void printSum(int a, int b = 4)
{
 cout << a + b << endl;
}
int main()
{
 printSum(13);
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Using Default Arguments[/h1]

Another example: [code format="cpp" codeId="245"]int volume(int l=1, int w=1, int h=1) {
  return l*w*h;
}

int main() {
  cout << volume() << endl;
  cout << volume(5) << endl;
  cout << volume(2, 3) << endl;
  cout << volume(3, 7, 6) << endl;
}

/* Output
1
5
6
126
*/[/code]
[note]As you can see, default parameter values can be used for calling the same function in different situations, when one or more of its parameters are not used.[/note]
